  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I have forgotten ssc cgl password, what should I do now?",
  "response": "If you've forgotten your SSC CGL (Staff Selection Commission Combined Graduate Level) password, don't worry\u2014you can reset it by following these steps:\n\n### **Step-by-Step Guide to Reset Your SSC CGL Password**\n\n1. **Visit the Official SSC Website:**\n   - Open your web browser and navigate to the official SSC portal: [https://ssc.nic.in](https://ssc.nic.in)\n\n2. **Navigate to the Login Page:**\n   - On the homepage, locate and click on the **\"CGL Login\"** option. This is typically found under the **\"Main Link\"** section or similar navigational areas.\n\n3. **Click on \"Forgot Password\":**\n   - On the login page, you'll see the **\"Forgot Password\"** link. Click on it to initiate the password reset process.\n\n4. **Enter Required Information:**\n   - You'll be prompted to enter details associated with your SSC CGL account. This may include:\n     - **User ID:** Your registered username.\n     - **Registration Number:** The number you received upon registering for SSC CGL.\n     - **Date of Birth:** As entered during registration.\n     - **Captcha Verification:** Complete the captcha to verify you're not a bot.\n\n5. **Submit the Information:**\n   - After filling in the necessary details, click on the **\"Submit\"** or **\"Generate OTP\"** button. An OTP (One-Time Password) will be sent to your registered mobile number or email address.\n\n6. **Enter the OTP:**\n   - Check your mobile phone or email for the OTP sent by SSC. Enter this OTP in the designated field on the website.\n\n7. **Reset Your Password:**\n   - Once the OTP is verified, you'll be prompted to create a new password. Ensure your new password is strong and secure\u2014ideally a mix of uppercase and lowercase letters, numbers, and special characters.\n\n8. **Confirm the New Password:**\n   - Re-enter your new password to confirm it. Make sure it matches the criteria specified by SSC.\n\n9. **Login with Your New Password:**\n   - After successfully resetting your password, return to the **CGL Login** page and sign in using your User ID and the newly created password.\n\n### **Additional Tips:**\n\n- **Use the Official Website:** Always ensure you're on the official SSC website ([https://ssc.nic.in](https://ssc.nic.in)) to avoid phishing scams.\n  \n- **Check Spam/Junk Folders:** If you don't receive the OTP via email, check your spam or junk folders.\n  \n- **Contact SSC Helpdesk if Needed:**\n  - If you encounter issues during the password reset process, you can reach out to the SSC helpdesk for assistance:\n    - **Phone:** +91-011-23335256 / +91-011-23335623\n    - **Email:** You can find specific contact emails on the [SSC Contact Us](https://ssc.nic.in/contacts.html) page.\n\n- **Maintain Updated Contact Information:** Ensure that your registered mobile number and email address are active and accessible, as the OTP will be sent to these for verification.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to regain access to your SSC CGL account. If problems persist, contacting the SSC directly is the best course of action to resolve any account-related issues.",
